# Frontend (MeetIQ)

## Stack

- Next.js 15 (App Router, Turbopack)
- TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS
- shadcn/ui (Radix-based primitives, CLI-installed into `src/components/ui`)
- Framer Motion for animation
- `lucide-react` for icons
- `next-themes` for dark/light mode

## Folder Structure

```
frontend/src/
  app/                       # Routes (App Router)
    (marketing)/             # Public marketing routes (landing, pricing)
    (auth)/                  # sign-in, sign-up
    (app)/                   # Authenticated app shell (dashboard, settings, etc.)
    meeting/[id]/            # Meeting room (its own layout)
  components/
    ui/                      # shadcn primitives (do not modify by hand)
    marketing/               # Landing page sections
    dashboard/
    meeting/
    shared/                  # Cross-feature components (Logo, ThemeToggle, etc.)
  lib/                       # utils, cn(), api client, hooks
  types/                     # Shared TS types (mirror backend contracts)
  styles/                    # globals.css only
```

## Design System

- **Colors**: Indigo/Blue primary, Purple accent, Slate neutrals. Defined as CSS variables in `globals.css`, exposed through Tailwind theme tokens.
- **Radius**: `rounded-xl` / `rounded-2xl` is the default for cards and buttons.
- **Surfaces**: Use subtle gradients + glassmorphism (`backdrop-blur`, semi-transparent borders) for hero/feature surfaces.
- **Typography**: `Inter` (body) + `Geist` or `Cal Sans` for display (loaded via `next/font`).
- **Motion**: Framer Motion `whileInView` for section reveals, `transition={{ duration: 0.5, ease: "easeOut" }}` as default.
- **Dark mode is default**. Light mode supported and polished, never an afterthought.

## Component Conventions

- Server Components by default. Add `"use client"` only when needed (state, effects, motion, event handlers).
- Co-locate small section components inside their feature folder; promote to `shared/` only when reused across features.
- Always use `cn()` from `lib/utils.ts` for conditional class names.
- Prefer composition over props explosion. If a component has more than ~8 props, split it.

## What NOT to do

- Don't hardcode colors — use Tailwind tokens / CSS variables.
- Don't import shadcn primitives from `@radix-ui/*` directly — go through `components/ui/*`.
- Don't add new global state libraries without approval (Zustand/Jotai are fine when needed).
- Don't make API calls in components — keep them in `lib/api/*` and call from server components or hooks.
